Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:01.68,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, to review,\N{\rChinese}好的，回顾一下，
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.92,0:00:07.50,English,,0,0,0,,last class we discussed three pre -historical sites,\N{\rChinese}上节课我们讨论了三个史前遗址，
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.64,0:00:12.36,English,,0,0,0,,right? Including Gobekli Tepe, Jericho, and Kanahoyak.\N{\rChinese}对吗？包括戈贝克利塔佩、耶利哥和卡纳霍亚克。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.87,0:00:17.12,English,,0,0,0,,And the argument I made to you last class,\N{\rChinese}我在上节课提出的论点，
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.14,0:00:20.12,English,,0,0,0,,which is the general scholarly consensus,\N{\rChinese}这已成为学界普遍共识，
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.12,0:00:21.82,English,,0,0,0,,is that\N{\rChinese}就是……
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.82,0:00:24.44,English,,0,0,0,,what drove,\N{\rChinese}驱动的是什么，
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.70,0:00:27.36,English,,0,0,0,,what compelled the transition\N{\rChinese}促使转向农业的是什么，
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.36,0:00:31.60,English,,0,0,0,,to agriculture was the religious\N{\rChinese}农业转变的驱动力是宗教
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.60,0:00:34.42,English,,0,0,0,,beliefs of the people at that time, okay?\N{\rChinese}那时人们的信仰，明白吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.58,0:00:37.80,English,,0,0,0,,So it was humanity's religious impulse that\N{\rChinese}于是正是人类的宗教冲动，驱使我们转向农业。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.80,0:00:42.94,English,,0,0,0,,drove our transition into agriculture.\N{\rChinese}drove our transition into agriculture.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.42,0:00:45.96,English,,0,0,0,,What I will show you today, okay,\N{\rChinese}我今天要给你们展示的内容，明白吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.04,0:00:48.44,English,,0,0,0,,my argument to you today is that\N{\rChinese}我今天的论点是：
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.44,0:00:51.96,English,,0,0,0,,this religious impulse, this need for religion,\N{\rChinese}这宗教冲动，这种对宗教的需求，
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.20,0:00:55.68,English,,0,0,0,,this need to understand why we are here today,\N{\rChinese}这份理解我们今天为何在此的需求，
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.88,0:00:58.68,English,,0,0,0,,and what we must be doing, and where we're going,\N{\rChinese}以及我们必须做什么、去向何方，
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.84,0:01:01.16,English,,0,0,0,,it's always been there, okay?\N{\rChinese}这一直都在，明白吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.34,0:01:05.64,English,,0,0,0,,In fact, religion is what makes us fundamentally human.\N{\rChinese}事实上，宗教是让我们本质上成为人的东西。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.04,0:01:07.66,English,,0,0,0,,And to prove this case,\N{\rChinese}为了证明这一点，
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.92,0:01:11.66,English,,0,0,0,,I'm going to talk about Ice Age cave paintings.\N{\rChinese}我将谈谈冰河时代的洞穴壁画。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.00,0:01:15.24,English,,0,0,0,,So I asked you to look at these cave paintings\N{\rChinese}于是我请你们看看这些我们在世界各地发现的洞穴壁画
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.24,0:01:17.58,English,,0,0,0,,that we found all around the world, okay?\N{\rChinese}它们可以追溯到三万四万年前。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.80,0:01:20.10,English,,0,0,0,,They go back 30,000, 40,000 years.\N{\rChinese}它们非常漂亮，对吧？并且极具创意与艺术性。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.42,0:01:26.06,English,,0,0,0,,And as you can see from those pictures,\N{\rChinese}如你从这些图片中看到的那样，
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.34,0:01:28.76,English,,0,0,0,,they're beautiful, right? And\N{\rChinese}它们很漂亮，对吧？而且
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.76,0:01:31.76,English,,0,0,0,,they're extremely creative, artistic.\N{\rChinese}它们极具创意与艺术性。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.16,0:01:37.12,English,,0,0,0,,And so I want to look at three questions about the cave paintings today.\N{\rChinese}于是我想今天先看三个关于洞穴壁画的问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.38,0:01:39.78,English,,0,0,0,,First of all, how were they painted?\N{\rChinese}首先，它们是怎么画的？
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.22,0:01:42.42,English,,0,0,0,,They didn't have the technology we have today, so\N{\rChinese}他们没有我们今天的技术，
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.42,0:01:45.70,English,,0,0,0,,how did they paint these cave paintings?\N{\rChinese}它们是怎么画的？
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.06,0:01:49.36,English,,0,0,0,,Second question is, why did they do this?\N{\rChinese}第二个问题是，为什么他们会这么做？
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.58,0:01:53.20,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. Because when you're in a cave, it's very dark,\N{\rChinese}好的。因为在洞里，光很暗，
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.34,0:01:56.24,English,,0,0,0,,it's very cold, and it's very hard to breathe.\N{\rChinese}它很冷，呼吸也很困难。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.72,0:02:01.26,English,,0,0,0,,But they spent days in there painting them.\N{\rChinese}但他们在那里花了几天时间去画。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.38,0:02:03.50,English,,0,0,0,,So why did they do that? That's the second question.\N{\rChinese}于是他们为什么这么做？这就是第二个问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.02,0:02:06.64,English,,0,0,0,,And the third question is, and\N{\rChinese}第三个问题是，且
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.64,0:02:10.72,English,,0,0,0,,the hardest question is, what do these cave paintings represent?\N{\rChinese}最难的问题是，这些洞穴壁画代表什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.22,0:02:12.84,English,,0,0,0,,Or what do they mean?\N{\rChinese}或者它们意味着什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.24,0:02:15.98,English,,0,0,0,,So the first caveat,\N{\rChinese}于是第一个前置点，
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.22,0:02:19.04,English,,0,0,0,,the first thing I want you to be aware of is that\N{\rChinese}我想让你先知道的第一件事是，
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.04,0:02:23.48,English,,0,0,0,,there's absolutely no agreement on any of these questions.\N{\rChinese}这些问题没有任何一致的答案。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.80,0:02:26.16,English,,0,0,0,,Cave paintings is something that\N{\rChinese}洞穴壁画是我们在世界各地都有的事物，
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.16,0:02:28.92,English,,0,0,0,,we have a lot of around the world,\N{\rChinese}我们在世界各地都有很多，
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.10,0:02:34.98,English,,0,0,0,,but there's very little evidence as to what they are,\N{\rChinese}但关于它们是什么的证据却很少。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.10,0:02:36.96,English,,0,0,0,,what they represent, and how they were painted.\N{\rChinese}它们所代表的意义，以及它们是如何绘制的。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.32,0:02:39.88,English,,0,0,0,,So there are a lot of guesses, okay?\N{\rChinese}于是有很多猜测，明白吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.12,0:02:41.04,English,,0,0,0,,And the case that\N{\rChinese}以及这个案例是
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.04,0:02:42.58,English,,0,0,0,,I will present to you today is\N{\rChinese}今天我要呈现给你的是
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.58,0:02:48.30,English,,0,0,0,,my own personal interpretation based on my research\N{\rChinese}我个人的解释，基于我的研究
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.30,0:02:49.88,English,,0,0,0,,and my understanding of the evidence.\N{\rChinese}以及我对证据的理解
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.08,0:02:52.32,English,,0,0,0,,But please be aware that\N{\rChinese}但请注意，
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.32,0:02:55.22,English,,0,0,0,,there are many different interpretations,\N{\rChinese}有许多不同的解释，
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.54,0:02:59.82,English,,0,0,0,,and the evidence is extremely unclear about many of these things, okay?\N{\rChinese}而关于这些事物的证据非常不清晰，明白吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.24,0:03:03.26,English,,0,0,0,,So let's start.\N{\rChinese}好了，开始吧。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.02,0:03:08.24,English,,0,0,0,,The first thing you need to understand is that\N{\rChinese}首先你需要理解的是：
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.08,0:03:16.70,English,,0,0,0,,for most of human history, it's been very cold, okay?\N{\rChinese}在大多数人类历史里，地球一直很冷，明白吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.70,0:03:21.66,English,,0,0,0,,So the Ice Age only ended about 12,000 years ago.\N{\rChinese}冰河期大约在1.2万年前结束。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.80,0:03:24.52,English,,0,0,0,,And we've seen a general warming of the planet,\N{\rChinese}随后地球出现了整体升温，
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.70,0:03:27.46,English,,0,0,0,,which has allowed us to adopt agriculture.\N{\rChinese}这使我们得以农耕为生。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.94,0:03:31.70,English,,0,0,0,,But before then, we're basically living on a very cold planet.\N{\rChinese}但在那之前，我们基本上是住在一个很冷的星球上。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.22,0:03:35.08,English,,0,0,0,,Now, the history of humanity is this.\N{\rChinese}现在，人类的历史就是这样。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.02,0:03:37.56,English,,0,0,0,,300,000 years ago,\N{\rChinese}三十万年前，
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.78,0:03:42.76,English,,0,0,0,,we came into being in Africa.\N{\rChinese}我们在非洲出现了存在。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.10,0:03:46.68,English,,0,0,0,,But because the world was cold,\N{\rChinese}但因为世界很冷，
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.70,0:03:49.20,English,,0,0,0,,became very cold about 100,000 years ago,\N{\rChinese}大约在一万年前变得很冷。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.06,0:03:51.86,English,,0,0,0,,that meant a scarcity of resources.\N{\rChinese}那意味着资源短缺。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.78,0:03:57.40,English,,0,0,0,,And that forced us to seek food and resources elsewhere.\N{\rChinese}于是我们被迫去别处寻找食物和资源。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.84,0:04:01.16,English,,0,0,0,,And so that drove our movement into Europe,\N{\rChinese}于是这推动了我们向欧洲的迁移。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.30,0:04:04.12,English,,0,0,0,,which then drove our movement into Asia,\N{\rChinese}随后推动我们向亚洲迁移，然后穿越白令海峡，记住这全是冰的，再往北美和南美。】
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.32,0:04:07.92,English,,0,0,0,,and then across the Bering Strait,\N{\rChinese}\}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.98,0:04:11.68,English,,0,0,0,,remember because this is all ice, right? Into North America and into South America.\N{\rChinese}\}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.98,0:04:14.78,English,,0,0,0,,And then from Asia, we went down to Australia, okay?\N{\rChinese}于是从亚洲我们又向澳大利亚迁移，明白吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.92,0:04:16.68,English,,0,0,0,,So we basically colonized Africa.\N{\rChinese}于是我们基本上殖民了非洲。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.16,0:04:20.80,English,,0,0,0,,We colonized the planet. But there were not many of us.\N{\rChinese}我们殖民了整个星球。但我们并不多。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.86,0:04:26.78,English,,0,0,0,,There was only about 1 million of us around the world 20,000 years ago.\N{\rChinese}大约两万年前，全球约有一百万人类。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.52,0:04:30.62,English,,0,0,0,,And the other thing to remember is that in this process,\N{\rChinese}另外要记住的是，在这个过程中，
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.04,0:04:33.78,English,,0,0,0,,there were actually other human beings in other places.\N{\rChinese}实际上还有其他人类在不同地方。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.00,0:04:35.62,English,,0,0,0,,So the Neanderthals were here.\N{\rChinese}所以尼安德尔人就在这里。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.84,0:04:39.20,English,,0,0,0,,The Nesavans were here.\N{\rChinese}所以尼萨凡人就在这里。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.30,0:04:44.50,English,,0,0,0,,And we interbred with them until we became the dominant human species,\N{\rChinese}我们与他们交配，直到成为主导人类。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.76,0:04:46.88,English,,0,0,0,,okay? So does that make sense?\N{\rChinese}好的？那样说通吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.40,0:04:49.44,English,,0,0,0,,All right, so that's the background.\N{\rChinese}好的，背景就这么说了。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.52,0:04:52.44,English,,0,0,0,,Now, let's look at some cave paintings.\N{\rChinese}现在，让我们看看一些洞穴壁画。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.10,0:04:56.56,English,,0,0,0,,Because this is in the Shovel Cave,\N{\rChinese}因为这在铲子洞里，并且它始于三万年前。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.98,0:04:59.70,English,,0,0,0,,and this started about 30,000 years ago.\N{\rChinese}所以这些洞穴壁画是一个连续的过程。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.92,0:05:01.96,English,,0,0,0,,So these cave paintings were a continuous process\N{\rChinese}So these cave paintingswere a continuous process
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.74,0:05:07.28,English,,0,0,0,,where different people at different times went to the caves and painted different pictures.\N{\rChinese}不同的人在不同的时间去洞穴画不同的图画。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.42,0:05:11.02,English,,0,0,0,,They might have added more things to the pictures as well, okay?\N{\rChinese}他们也可能在图画里再加上其他东西，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.22,0:05:12.66,English,,0,0,0,,But as you can see,\N{\rChinese}但你可以看到，
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.66,0:05:16.98,English,,0,0,0,,this is clearly representing animals, right?\N{\rChinese}这明显是动物的描绘，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.10,0:05:19.34,English,,0,0,0,,Bisons, rhinoceros.\N{\rChinese}野牛，犀牛。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.72,0:05:22.96,English,,0,0,0,,The other thing that's interesting about these paintings is that\N{\rChinese}另外一个有趣的点是这些画作的……
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.56,0:05:27.76,English,,0,0,0,,there's really no focus, okay?\N{\rChinese}没有特别聚焦，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.24,0:05:30.10,English,,0,0,0,,You see lions.\N{\rChinese}你看见狮子。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.36,0:05:31.78,English,,0,0,0,,You see horses.\N{\rChinese}你看见马。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.98,0:05:34.40,English,,0,0,0,,You see rhinos, okay?\N{\rChinese}你看见犀牛，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.50,0:05:38.70,English,,0,0,0,,It's almost like nature is one interconnected picture,\N{\rChinese}就像大自然是一幅连贯的画面，
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.10,0:05:40.24,English,,0,0,0,,okay?\N{\rChinese}行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.10,0:05:46.40,English,,0,0,0,,These are lions,\N{\rChinese}这些是狮子，
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.76,0:05:48.28,English,,0,0,0,,okay?\N{\rChinese}行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.96,0:05:53.02,English,,0,0,0,,This is Lacolle Cave about 20,000 years ago.\N{\rChinese}这是拉科尔洞穴，约二万年前。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.32,0:05:54.64,English,,0,0,0,,And the most...\N{\rChinese}以及最…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.64,0:05:56.56,English,,0,0,0,,And a very famous artist, Papa Picasso,\N{\rChinese}以及一位非常著名的画家，帕帕·毕加索，
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.86,0:05:59.78,English,,0,0,0,,actually was invited into one of these caves,\N{\rChinese}实际上被邀请到其中一座洞穴里
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.94,0:06:01.38,English,,0,0,0,,and he said that, wow,\N{\rChinese}并且他说了，哇，
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.66,0:06:05.18,English,,0,0,0,,we learned nothing in 10,000 years,\N{\rChinese}我们在一万年里学不到什么，
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.40,0:06:09.30,English,,0,0,0,,meaning that they were just as good back\N{\rChinese}也就是说他们当时也一样好
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.30,0:06:10.96,English,,0,0,0,,then as they are today.\N{\rChinese}然后就像今天一样。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.96,0:06:12.36,English,,0,0,0,,Artistically speaking,\N{\rChinese}从艺术角度说，
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.76,0:06:15.62,English,,0,0,0,,humans have not improved at all, okay?\N{\rChinese}人类一点也没进步，嗯？
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.00,0:06:26.40,English,,0,0,0,,So these are horses, okay?\N{\rChinese}于是这些是马，嗯？
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.84,0:06:31.68,English,,0,0,0,,This is Altamira, Spain, which goes back to 34,000 BCE.\N{\rChinese}这是阿尔塔米拉，西班牙，追溯到公元前34,000年。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.28,0:06:36.46,English,,0,0,0,,And you can see that\N{\rChinese}你可以看到的
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.46,0:06:40.74,English,,0,0,0,,they're not looking for a realistic depiction of animals, okay?\N{\rChinese}他们并不是想要动物的逼真描绘，嗯？
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.74,0:06:44.86,English,,0,0,0,,They're trying to imagine the natural\N{\rChinese}他们正试着想象自然
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.86,0:06:48.14,English,,0,0,0,,world in their own way, okay?\N{\rChinese}以自己的方式呈现世界，嗯？
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.22,0:06:50.40,English,,0,0,0,,So another question then is, okay,\N{\rChinese}那么还有一个问题，嗯？
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.60,0:06:54.94,English,,0,0,0,,how did they paint these pictures?\N{\rChinese}他们是怎么画这些图的？
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.12,0:07:00.58,English,,0,0,0,,So first of all, they mainly used red and black, okay?\N{\rChinese}首先，他们主要用红色和黑色，嗯？
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.68,0:07:03.48,English,,0,0,0,,Red came from ochre, which is a type of clay,\N{\rChinese}红色来自赭土，这是一种粘土，嗯？
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.72,0:07:06.62,English,,0,0,0,,and black comes from a charcoal, okay?\N{\rChinese}黑色来自木炭，嗯？
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.66,0:07:08.56,English,,0,0,0,,So that's the coloring they used.\N{\rChinese}于是他们就用这种颜色来着色。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.96,0:07:14.82,English,,0,0,0,,Inside a cave, it's very dark,\N{\rChinese}在洞穴里很黑暗，
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.02,0:07:17.48,English,,0,0,0,,so they had to use lighting, okay?\N{\rChinese}于是他们就用灯光照明，嗯？
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.64,0:07:21.86,English,,0,0,0,,So what they did was they got some animal fat and put fire on it, okay?\N{\rChinese}他们做的就是取一些动物脂肪点火，嗯？
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.90,0:07:26.50,English,,0,0,0,,So they could see some of the caves,\N{\rChinese}于是他们能看到一些洞穴，
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.72,0:07:29.26,English,,0,0,0,,but not all of them, okay?\N{\rChinese}但并不是全部，嗯？
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.96,0:07:33.60,English,,0,0,0,,And then... So another question is,\N{\rChinese}然后……还有一个问题是，
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.50,0:07:37.00,English,,0,0,0,,why did they paint these pictures?\N{\rChinese}他们为什么画这些图画？
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.46,0:07:39.32,English,,0,0,0,,And a lot of the clue is this.\N{\rChinese}很多线索就在这里。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.78,0:07:42.64,English,,0,0,0,,A lot of the clue is this. One clue is where\N{\rChinese}很多线索就在这里。一个线索是位置。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.64,0:07:45.40,English,,0,0,0,,we found these paintings.\N{\rChinese}我们发现了这些画作。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.72,0:07:49.82,English,,0,0,0,,We found these paintings in a very special place in the cave.\N{\rChinese}我们在洞穴的一个非常特殊的地方发现了这些画作。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.42,0:07:53.88,English,,0,0,0,,We found these paintings in the cave, a section of the cave\N{\rChinese}我们在洞穴里发现了这些画作，一段洞穴的区域。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.88,0:07:57.10,English,,0,0,0,,where the acoustics was the best, the sound was the best.\N{\rChinese}在声学最好的地方，声音也最棒。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.62,0:08:01.00,English,,0,0,0,,So what this means is we're fairly convinced\N{\rChinese}这意味着我们相当确定
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.72,0:08:06.72,English,,0,0,0,,that these paintings were part of a ritual\N{\rChinese}这些画作是仪式的一部分。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.72,0:08:09.78,English,,0,0,0,,which included music, because\N{\rChinese}包括音乐，因而如此。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.78,0:08:12.98,English,,0,0,0,,we found these paintings in musical instruments as well, flutes, okay?\N{\rChinese}我们在乐器里也找到了这些画作，长笛之类，嗯？
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.58,0:08:16.18,English,,0,0,0,,So in other words, we think that\N{\rChinese}所以换句话说，我们认为
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.18,0:08:20.16,English,,0,0,0,,these paintings are like Gopalpepepe,\N{\rChinese}这些画作像Gopalpepepe一样，
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.54,0:08:23.28,English,,0,0,0,,which is like maybe now and then\N{\rChinese}这就像现在和那时一样，
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.28,0:08:25.98,English,,0,0,0,,these hunter -gatherers would come into\N{\rChinese}这些狩猎采集者会来到
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.98,0:08:29.60,English,,0,0,0,,this cave for a religious festival\N{\rChinese}这座洞穴用于宗教节庆
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.60,0:08:32.88,English,,0,0,0,,where there's music, dancing, okay?\N{\rChinese}有音乐、舞蹈，嗯？
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.08,0:08:39.06,English,,0,0,0,,And they are watching these paintings together.\N{\rChinese}他们一起观赏这些画作
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.06,0:08:43.36,English,,0,0,0,,So these paintings are part of a religious festival.\N{\rChinese}这些画作是宗教节庆的一部分。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.58,0:08:47.40,English,,0,0,0,,In other words, these paintings are not about art.\N{\rChinese}换句话说，这些画作不只是艺术。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.54,0:08:49.38,English,,0,0,0,,It's really about religion.\N{\rChinese}它们真正是关于宗教的。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.64,0:08:54.00,English,,0,0,0,,It's expressing the religious beliefs of the people at\N{\rChinese}它表达了当时人们的宗教信仰
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.00,0:08:55.20,English,,0,0,0,,that time, okay?\N{\rChinese}那时的情况，嗯？
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.56,0:08:57.32,English,,0,0,0,,So does this make sense, guys?\N{\rChinese}这样说通吗，大家？
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.56,0:08:59.96,English,,0,0,0,,All right. Yes?\N{\rChinese}好的。对吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.02,0:09:09.90,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, so I'm going to answer the question, what are the beliefs right now, okay?\N{\rChinese}好的，我来回答问题：现在的信仰是什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.00,0:09:12.50,English,,0,0,0,,All right. So again,\N{\rChinese}好的。再说一次，
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.62,0:09:17.18,English,,0,0,0,,no one knows what their beliefs are because they wrote nothing down, okay?\N{\rChinese}没有人知道他们的信仰是什么，因为他们没有写下来，嗯？
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.30,0:09:18.72,English,,0,0,0,,They are preliterate.\N{\rChinese}他们是前文字社会。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.12,0:09:22.96,English,,0,0,0,,We can't go back in time and talk to them, okay?\N{\rChinese}我们无法回到过去去和他们对话，嗯？
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.92,0:09:26.70,English,,0,0,0,,So we have to use our imagination.\N{\rChinese}于是我们就要用想象力。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.58,0:09:29.96,English,,0,0,0,,So let's imagine that we go to a temple and\N{\rChinese}于是我们想象去一座寺庙，去……
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.96,0:09:32.68,English,,0,0,0,,we go back in time to this time.\N{\rChinese}我们回到那个时代。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.82,0:09:35.06,English,,0,0,0,,It's very cold and\N{\rChinese}很冷，且
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.06,0:09:36.96,English,,0,0,0,,our memories have been wiped out,\N{\rChinese}我们的记忆被抹去，
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.10,0:09:39.92,English,,0,0,0,,meaning like we've lost the knowledge of today.\N{\rChinese}就像我们失去了今天的知识。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.18,0:09:41.38,English,,0,0,0,,We've lost science.\N{\rChinese}我们已经失去了科学。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.70,0:09:45.28,English,,0,0,0,,We've lost what we learned in biology class, okay?\N{\rChinese}我们已经失去了生物课上学到的东西，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.14,0:09:49.32,English,,0,0,0,,So my first question is, we're in this world\N{\rChinese}于是我的第一个问题是，我们现在处在这个世界里
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.96,0:09:53.28,English,,0,0,0,,and what are things that amaze us\N{\rChinese}以及让我们惊叹的事物
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.86,0:09:56.24,English,,0,0,0,,or make us wonder or make us in awe?\N{\rChinese}或让我们惊奇、敬畏的事物？
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.48,0:09:59.34,English,,0,0,0,,What are things that capture our imagination?\N{\rChinese}是什么能捕捉我们想象的事物？
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.06,0:10:03.10,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Meaning like we see these things and\N{\rChinese}好的？就像我们看到这些事物时，
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.10,0:10:06.18,English,,0,0,0,,we're like, oh my God, God must exist because\N{\rChinese}我们会说，哦我的天啊，神一定存在，因为
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.18,0:10:08.80,English,,0,0,0,,there's no way I can explain what happened.\N{\rChinese}没有办法解释发生的事。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.66,0:10:11.38,English,,0,0,0,,What are these things that we would see\N{\rChinese}这些事物是什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.78,0:10:14.40,English,,0,0,0,,and we would be surprised by,\N{\rChinese}我们会看到并感到惊讶的事物
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.64,0:10:16.82,English,,0,0,0,,marvel at,\N{\rChinese}我们会惊叹的事物
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.48,0:10:18.88,English,,0,0,0,,basically be in awe of?\N{\rChinese}基本是惊叹于？
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.40,0:10:21.50,English,,0,0,0,,What are things about our life that amazes us?\N{\rChinese}关于我们生活中让我们惊叹的事物是什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.18,0:10:24.76,English,,0,0,0,,What's the first thing that we can think of?\N{\rChinese}我们能想到的第一件事是什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.44,0:10:36.52,English,,0,0,0,,What's the first thing? You're in this world,\N{\rChinese}第一件事是什么？你在这个世界里，
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.58,0:10:40.32,English,,0,0,0,,right? Use your imagination. What's one thing that's like, oh, okay,\N{\rChinese}对吧？发挥你的想象。有什么一件事，像是，哦，好，
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.22,0:10:45.30,English,,0,0,0,,there must be a God or there must be some supernatural powers\N{\rChinese}一定有神或者有超自然的力量
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.76,0:10:48.90,English,,0,0,0,,that govern our world. What's the first thing that comes to mind?\N{\rChinese}那些支配我们世界的事物。先想到的是什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.96,0:10:55.62,English,,0,0,0,,How about childbirth? Childbirth, right?\N{\rChinese}关于分娩？分娩，对吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.28,0:10:59.54,English,,0,0,0,,Does that make sense to you guys?\N{\rChinese}这对你们来说有意义吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.52,0:11:02.46,English,,0,0,0,,Because I'm a father, I have three kids.\N{\rChinese}因为我是个父亲，我有三个孩子。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.50,0:11:05.66,English,,0,0,0,,And I can tell you, when\N{\rChinese}我可以告诉你，当……
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.66,0:11:09.48,English,,0,0,0,,I first saw my child being born, I was amazed.\N{\rChinese}我第一次看到我的孩子出生时，我很惊讶。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.78,0:11:12.96,English,,0,0,0,,Because you have this life come out of nothing, right?\N{\rChinese}因为你有这生命从无中诞生，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.82,0:11:19.12,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And if you don't, if you never studied biology, you can't explain what happened.\N{\rChinese}好？如果你没有，若你从未学过生物学，你就无法解释发生了什么。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.70,0:11:22.54,English,,0,0,0,,So that's the first thing that amazes about,\N{\rChinese}于是这就是第一个让人惊叹的事物。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.74,0:11:25.00,English,,0,0,0,,amazes us about being human.\N{\rChinese}让我们惊叹的是人类的存在。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.10,0:11:26.34,English,,0,0,0,,Childbirth. Childbirth, right?\N{\rChinese}出生。出生，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.74,0:11:30.76,English,,0,0,0,,What's the second thing that would amaze you if you were back here?\N{\rChinese}如果你回到这里，第二件让你惊叹的事是什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.66,0:11:36.14,English,,0,0,0,,Child growing up. Okay, so child growing up.\N{\rChinese}孩子长大。好了，孩子长大。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.00,0:11:39.06,English,,0,0,0,,Yes. What else?\N{\rChinese}是的。还有什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.60,0:11:47.04,English,,0,0,0,,How about, yeah? Okay, how about the stars, right?\N{\rChinese}怎么样，嗯？好了，星星怎么样，吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.36,0:11:51.12,English,,0,0,0,,It's late at night.\N{\rChinese}夜已深。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.26,0:11:52.68,English,,0,0,0,,And remember, there's no pollution.\N{\rChinese}记得，没污染。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.72,0:11:56.90,English,,0,0,0,,So you see out into the darkness,\N{\rChinese}你望向黑暗。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.02,0:11:59.48,English,,0,0,0,,and it's all stars glowing, right?\N{\rChinese}而且全是星星发光，对吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.68,0:12:04.34,English,,0,0,0,,That's pretty amazing. So what do you think these stars are?\N{\rChinese}真是太神奇了。那么你觉得这些星星是什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.76,0:12:11.88,English,,0,0,0,,You're staring out into outer space, right?\N{\rChinese}你正望向外太空，对吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.00,0:12:14.76,English,,0,0,0,,And you see these stars glowing brightly in the sky.\N{\rChinese}你看到天空中这些星星闪耀着光芒。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.96,0:12:18.44,English,,0,0,0,,What are they? What's your own explanation, really?\N{\rChinese}它们是什么？你自己的解释是什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.40,0:12:20.78,English,,0,0,0,,..\N{\rChinese}…
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.50,0:12:25.64,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, possibly, okay?\N{\rChinese}好的，可能，好的？
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.80,0:12:29.32,English,,0,0,0,,Possibly souls or other worlds, okay?\N{\rChinese}可能是灵魂或其他世界，好的？
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.36,0:12:32.14,English,,0,0,0,,Planets, worlds. In other words,\N{\rChinese}行星，世界。换句话说，
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.14,0:12:35.00,English,,0,0,0,,the first thing that you recognize is\N{\rChinese}第一个你会认出的事物是
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.00,0:12:39.90,English,,0,0,0,,that our world is just one of many worlds out there.\N{\rChinese}我们的世界只是众多世界中的一个而已。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.46,0:12:43.14,English,,0,0,0,,Does that make sense? All right?\N{\rChinese}这样说通吗？好了？
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.58,0:12:49.18,English,,0,0,0,,What else amazes you about the world?\N{\rChinese}还有什么让你惊叹世界？
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.16,0:12:53.16,English,,0,0,0,,. Excuse me?\N{\rChinese}请问一下？
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.56,0:12:56.22,English,,0,0,0,,. Okay, recovery from disease.\N{\rChinese}好的，疾病康复。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.44,0:12:59.28,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, so healing, right?\N{\rChinese}好的，治愈对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.66,0:13:03.56,English,,0,0,0,,How do you explain healing, then?\N{\rChinese}那你怎么解释治愈？
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.14,0:13:06.86,English,,0,0,0,,. What thoughts save you?\N{\rChinese}什么想法能救你？
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.36,0:13:11.20,English,,0,0,0,,. Oh, that God saved you.\N{\rChinese}哦，神救了你。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.46,0:13:13.26,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, all right, yeah, okay.\N{\rChinese}好的，没问题，好的。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.38,0:13:15.60,English,,0,0,0,,So there are some supernatural powers.\N{\rChinese}于是有些超自然的力量。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.60,0:13:20.34,English,,0,0,0,,. But\N{\rChinese}. 但
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.34,0:13:23.46,English,,0,0,0,,another way to explain healing, okay, is\N{\rChinese}另一种解释治愈的方式，好的，就是
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.46,0:13:27.82,English,,0,0,0,,that you have a body and you have a soul, right?\N{\rChinese}你有身体也有灵魂，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.96,0:13:30.34,English,,0,0,0,,And the soul could be one of the stars.\N{\rChinese}而灵魂也许是星辰之一。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.94,0:13:35.42,English,,0,0,0,,So what's causing disease in this world is the soul\N{\rChinese}于是这世界的病因是灵魂与身体的冲突。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.42,0:13:37.54,English,,0,0,0,,and the body are in conflict.\N{\rChinese}灵魂与身体相互冲突。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.10,0:13:41.00,English,,0,0,0,,And so healing is about bringing the soul and\N{\rChinese}而治愈就是让灵魂与身体合一齐，好的？
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.00,0:13:43.10,English,,0,0,0,,the body aligned together, okay?\N{\rChinese}而我们之所以这么想，是看中国医术，没错吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.22,0:13:47.72,English,,0,0,0,,. And we think this because look at Chinese medicine, right?\N{\rChinese}. And we think this because look at Chinese medicine, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.68,0:13:50.54,English,,0,0,0,,It's the same idea, right?\N{\rChinese}就是同样的想法，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.60,0:13:53.54,English,,0,0,0,,Where the soul and the body are in conflict, right?\N{\rChinese}灵魂与身体相互冲突，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.62,0:13:56.92,English,,0,0,0,,And you want to align the two in order to heal,\N{\rChinese}你想把两者合一齐以治愈，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.06,0:13:58.58,English,,0,0,0,,okay?\N{\rChinese}好的？
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.06,0:14:02.72,English,,0,0,0,,So other things that would surprise you is nature, right?\N{\rChinese}还有其他会让你惊讶的事是自然，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.24,0:14:05.02,English,,0,0,0,,The animals, the trees,\N{\rChinese}动物，树木，
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.20,0:14:09.34,English,,0,0,0,,the vastness of nature, okay?\N{\rChinese}自然的广阔，好的？
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.52,0:14:11.72,English,,0,0,0,,..\N{\rChinese}…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.72,0:14:13.54,English,,0,0,0,,And the things that surprise us.\N{\rChinese}以及让我们惊讶的事物。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.64,0:14:17.38,English,,0,0,0,,And they force us to ask the question, why?\N{\rChinese}于是他们逼我们去问，为什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.22,0:14:23.36,English,,0,0,0,,So now let's try to construct a theory of how to connect all these things,\N{\rChinese}现在让我们试着构造一个理论，连接这些事物，
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.50,0:14:26.50,English,,0,0,0,,okay? All right, so we know\N{\rChinese}好了，知道了
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.50,0:14:31.14,English,,0,0,0,,that the stars, there's other powers out there,\N{\rChinese}星星之中，那里还有其他力量，
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.20,0:14:33.60,English,,0,0,0,,right? There has to be gods or the\N{\rChinese}对吧？一定有神或者…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.60,0:14:39.16,English,,0,0,0,,soul of really great people or other planets or other worlds,\N{\rChinese}伟人之魂，或其他行星，或其他世界，
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.22,0:14:42.90,English,,0,0,0,,okay?. How does childbirth happen, then?\N{\rChinese}好了吗？孩子出生是怎么回事？
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.06,0:14:46.54,English,,0,0,0,,How does childbirth happen?\N{\rChinese}孩子出生是怎么回事？
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.88,0:14:52.26,English,,0,0,0,,How does childbirth happen? What is the womb?\N{\rChinese}孩子出生是怎么回事？子宫是什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.70,0:14:54.00,English,,0,0,0,,It comes from the womb, right?\N{\rChinese}它来自子宫，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.28,0:14:57.06,English,,0,0,0,,What's the womb, then?.\N{\rChinese}子宫是什么呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.86,0:15:02.84,English,,0,0,0,,A portal, a door, right?\N{\rChinese}一个门户，一个门，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.42,0:15:07.08,English,,0,0,0,,. So,\N{\rChinese}. 那么，
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.08,0:15:10.08,English,,0,0,0,,what the womb is, is a door, right?\N{\rChinese}子宫是什么， 就是一个门，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.10,0:15:11.58,English,,0,0,0,,portal that\N{\rChinese}一个门户
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.58,0:15:15.74,English,,0,0,0,,the soul comes from another world into our world.\N{\rChinese}灵魂从另一个世界来到我们的世界。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.10,0:15:19.24,English,,0,0,0,,Does that make sense? Then\N{\rChinese}这有道理吗？然后
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.24,0:15:23.10,English,,0,0,0,,how do people return to the other world?\N{\rChinese}人们是怎么回到另一个世界的？
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.26,0:15:27.64,English,,0,0,0,,If the womb is a portal\N{\rChinese}如果子宫是一个门户
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.64,0:15:30.24,English,,0,0,0,,that allows souls to come into our world,\N{\rChinese}让灵魂进入我们的世界
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.48,0:15:33.68,English,,0,0,0,,how do these souls return to their world again?\N{\rChinese}这些灵魂又如何回到自己的世界？
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.08,0:15:37.90,English,,0,0,0,,But what do they do in death?\N{\rChinese}但他们在死亡时做了什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.12,0:15:42.86,English,,0,0,0,,How do we...\N{\rChinese}我们是怎么做的……
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.86,0:15:45.04,English,,0,0,0,,so people die and then?\N{\rChinese}于是人们死去，然后呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.40,0:15:47.86,English,,0,0,0,,Burial. Thank you. Do you understand?\N{\rChinese}安葬。谢谢。你明白了吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.28,0:15:50.08,English,,0,0,0,,So this is symmetry, right?\N{\rChinese}所以这就是对称，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.74,0:15:56.74,English,,0,0,0,,The soul comes into our world from the mother's womb,\N{\rChinese}灵魂从母亲的子宫进入我们的世界
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.94,0:15:59.06,English,,0,0,0,,from darkness, and then\N{\rChinese}从黑暗中，随后
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.06,0:16:03.40,English,,0,0,0,,for us to return the soul back into the original world,\N{\rChinese}让我们把灵魂送回原始世界
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.40,0:16:06.68,English,,0,0,0,,we bury this person in darkness,\N{\rChinese}我们把此人葬于黑暗
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.96,0:16:11.18,English,,0,0,0,,and that carries that person back to the original world.\N{\rChinese}并把那个人送回原始世界。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.46,0:16:13.78,English,,0,0,0,,Does that make sense? So\N{\rChinese}这有道理吗？所以
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.78,0:16:18.20,English,,0,0,0,,this is probably the simplest explanation for how life and death works.\N{\rChinese}这大概是最简单的解释，说明生命与死亡的运作。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.02,0:16:25.14,English,,0,0,0,,So there are these portals,\N{\rChinese}于是就有这些通道，
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.16,0:16:29.94,English,,0,0,0,,and what in nature most resembles a womb?\N{\rChinese}以及自然界中最像子宫的是什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.00,0:16:33.38,English,,0,0,0,,What in nature most resembles a womb?\N{\rChinese}自然界中最像子宫的是什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.38,0:16:34.96,English,,0,0,0,,What in nature most resembles a womb?\N{\rChinese}自然界中最像子宫的是什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.78,0:16:40.52,English,,0,0,0,,A mother's womb. Like a cave, right?\N{\rChinese}母亲的子宫。像个洞穴，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.60,0:16:42.34,English,,0,0,0,,You understand? A cave.\N{\rChinese}你明白吗？一个洞穴。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.96,0:16:45.20,English,,0,0,0,,A mother's womb.\N{\rChinese}母亲的子宫。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.20,0:16:46.98,English,,0,0,0,,Like a cave, right? You understand? A cave. So we can think that, okay,\N{\rChinese}像个洞穴，对吧？你明白吗？一个洞穴。这样我们可以这么想，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.08,0:16:51.54,English,,0,0,0,,we humans come from a mother's womb,\N{\rChinese}我们人类来自母亲的子宫。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.64,0:16:53.60,English,,0,0,0,,which is a cave, right? A tunnel.\N{\rChinese}哪是个洞穴，对吧？一条隧道。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.06,0:16:59.20,English,,0,0,0,,But animals also come from a womb,\N{\rChinese}但动物也来自子宫，
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.32,0:17:00.90,English,,0,0,0,,which is the cave, okay?\N{\rChinese}哪是个洞穴，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.18,0:17:05.68,English,,0,0,0,,So the cave is a portal into another world.\N{\rChinese}于是洞穴就是通往另一世界的门户。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.54,0:17:09.60,English,,0,0,0,,So why are we in the cave celebrating animals?\N{\rChinese}那我们为什么要在洞穴里庆祝动物呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.08,0:17:12.14,English,,0,0,0,,Why are we doing that?\N{\rChinese}我们为什么要这么做呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.38,0:17:18.38,English,,0,0,0,,Why are we in\N{\rChinese}我们为什么在
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.38,0:17:24.34,English,,0,0,0,,a cave celebrating animals?\N{\rChinese}洞穴里庆祝动物？
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.72,0:17:28.08,English,,0,0,0,,What are we really doing? We respect the soul?\N{\rChinese}我们到底在做什么？我们在尊敬灵魂吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.86,0:17:30.10,English,,0,0,0,,We respect what?\N{\rChinese}我们在尊敬什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.86,0:17:32.24,English,,0,0,0,,We respect the soul? We respect the soul?\N{\rChinese}我们在尊敬灵魂？我们在尊敬灵魂？
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.34,0:17:33.82,English,,0,0,0,,We respect the soul? what else are we doing?\N{\rChinese}我们在尊敬灵魂？我们还在做什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.94,0:17:36.56,English,,0,0,0,,Because, why are we respecting their soul?\N{\rChinese}因为，为什么我们在尊敬他们的灵魂？
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.70,0:17:42.94,English,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we kill them, right?\N{\rChinese}是的，我们杀了他们，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.86,0:17:46.82,English,,0,0,0,,So we kill them, and now what are we trying to do?\N{\rChinese}于是我们杀了他们，现在我们想做什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.22,0:17:53.90,English,,0,0,0,,Let them forgive us, but what else are we really trying to do?\N{\rChinese}让他们原谅我们，但我们真正想做的又是什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.68,0:17:57.82,English,,0,0,0,,Once we eat them, what must we do now?\N{\rChinese}吃完他们后，我们接下来要做什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.42,0:18:04.48,English,,0,0,0,,Excuse me? Yes,\N{\rChinese}请问一下？是的？
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.74,0:18:06.08,English,,0,0,0,,bring them back, right? Do you understand?\N{\rChinese}把他们召回，行吗？你明白了吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.62,0:18:10.86,English,,0,0,0,,So we kill them, we think they go back into the spirit world, right?\N{\rChinese}于是我们杀了他们，认为他们回到灵界，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.36,0:18:13.56,English,,0,0,0,,So now we have to summon them back\N{\rChinese}现在我们要把他们召回去。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.78,0:18:18.56,English,,0,0,0,,from the spirit world into our world.\N{\rChinese}从灵界回到我们的世界。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.46,0:18:20.66,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, does that make sense?\N{\rChinese}好的，这样说通吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.02,0:18:23.82,English,,0,0,0,,So, in other words,\N{\rChinese}也就是说，
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.90,0:18:28.40,English,,0,0,0,,what this religion, what this belief is really saying is\N{\rChinese}这宗教、这信仰真正表达的是
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.40,0:18:30.96,English,,0,0,0,,that we are all interconnected.\N{\rChinese}我们彼此相连。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.96,0:18:35.40,English,,0,0,0,,And for every action that we make,\N{\rChinese}而我们每一次行动都如此。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.81,0:18:38.78,English,,0,0,0,,we have to do something else to compensate for action, okay?\N{\rChinese}我们还得做点别的事来补偿行动，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.88,0:18:42.54,English,,0,0,0,,So if we kill an animal to eat the meat,\N{\rChinese}于是如果我们杀了动物吃肉，
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.72,0:18:45.94,English,,0,0,0,,then we need to ask forgiveness\N{\rChinese}那就得请个赎罪
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.94,0:18:50.26,English,,0,0,0,,and then bring this animal back into the spirit world to maintain balance\N{\rChinese}然后把这只动物送回灵界，以维持自然的平衡与和谐
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.26,0:18:51.74,English,,0,0,0,,and harmony in nature.\N{\rChinese}这有道理吗，大家？好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.40,0:18:54.68,English,,0,0,0,,Does that make sense, guys? Okay?\N{\rChinese}Does that make sense, guys? Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.13,0:18:58.82,English,,0,0,0,,So, why is it in this world\N{\rChinese}那么，为什么它在这个世界里呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.66,0:19:00.88,English,,0,0,0,,there's balance and harmony?\N{\rChinese}有平衡与和谐吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.94,0:19:03.46,English,,0,0,0,,Why do we think there's balance and harmony?\N{\rChinese}我们为什么认为有平衡与和谐？
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.94,0:19:08.24,English,,0,0,0,,Because what gives life to everything?\N{\rChinese}因为是什么赋予万物生命的力量？
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.54,0:19:11.16,English,,0,0,0,,What's the force that gives life to everything?\N{\rChinese}是什么力量赋予万物生命？
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.76,0:19:16.06,English,,0,0,0,,The mother goddess, right?\N{\rChinese}母神，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.14,0:19:17.64,English,,0,0,0,,Mother nature, okay?\N{\rChinese}母自然，好的？
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.86,0:19:22.00,English,,0,0,0,,And so, if we think that there's one force,\N{\rChinese}于是，如果我们认为有一种力量，
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.12,0:19:26.50,English,,0,0,0,,the mother goddess, that gives life to everything, that means that for us, trees,\N{\rChinese}母神，赋予万物生命，那就意味着对我们、树木而言，
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.36,0:19:29.48,English,,0,0,0,,animals, us, are all equal.\N{\rChinese}动物、我们、都平等。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.58,0:19:30.94,English,,0,0,0,,We're all the children of mother nature.\N{\rChinese}我们都是母自然的孩子。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.94,0:19:32.16,English,,0,0,0,,We all have souls,\N{\rChinese}我们都有灵魂，
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.60,0:19:37.34,English,,0,0,0,,okay? And so, what gives us permission to kill other animals?\N{\rChinese}好了？于是，是什么给我们杀其他动物的许可？
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.14,0:19:44.28,English,,0,0,0,,Why are we allowed to kill other animals?\N{\rChinese}为什么我们可以杀其他动物？
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.76,0:19:46.34,English,,0,0,0,,The other animals are\N{\rChinese}其他动物是
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.42,0:19:49.00,English,,0,0,0,,our brothers and sisters, right?\N{\rChinese}我们的兄弟姐妹，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.82,0:19:52.18,English,,0,0,0,,So what gives us permission to kill the other animals?\N{\rChinese}于是，是什么给我们杀其他动物的许可？
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.56,0:19:53.76,English,,0,0,0,,Why are we allowed to do so?\N{\rChinese}为什么我们可以这么做？
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.32,0:19:59.52,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, because\N{\rChinese}好的，因为
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.30,0:20:03.10,English,,0,0,0,,mother nature, mother goddess has a plan, okay?\N{\rChinese}大自然，母神有计划，好的？
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.92,0:20:07.86,English,,0,0,0,,Each thing on this planet has a function.\N{\rChinese}地球上的每件事物都有功能。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.06,0:20:10.08,English,,0,0,0,,The function is to maintain balance and harmony.\N{\rChinese}功能是维持平衡与和谐。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.62,0:20:14.58,English,,0,0,0,,If we do not kill the other animals, we will die, okay?\N{\rChinese}若不杀其他动物，我们就会死，明白吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.88,0:20:17.00,English,,0,0,0,,But also, if we don't kill the other animals,\N{\rChinese}又若不杀其他动物，
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.32,0:20:19.80,English,,0,0,0,,there'll be too many of them.\N{\rChinese}有太多了。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.02,0:20:22.40,English,,0,0,0,,You understand? So, in other words,\N{\rChinese}你明白吗？换句话说，
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.56,0:20:25.32,English,,0,0,0,,the world is a cycle, it's a circle,\N{\rChinese}世界是循环的，像个圆圈。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.84,0:20:27.30,English,,0,0,0,,and each person,\N{\rChinese}和每个人，
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.08,0:20:30.92,English,,0,0,0,,each animal, has a part to play in that.\N{\rChinese}每只动物都有自己的角色要扮演。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.92,0:20:34.02,English,,0,0,0,,And as long as we play our part, then\N{\rChinese}只要我们扮演好自己的角色，
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.02,0:20:37.68,English,,0,0,0,,the world will be harmonious, and balanced, and perfect, okay?\N{\rChinese}世界将和谐、平衡、完美，怎么样？
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.84,0:20:42.90,English,,0,0,0,,Does that make sense? Okay?\N{\rChinese}这样说通吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.54,0:20:45.96,English,,0,0,0,,Does that make sense, guys? Okay, so,\N{\rChinese}这样说通吗，大家？
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.32,0:20:51.04,English,,0,0,0,,we have, actually, a word for this religion,\N{\rChinese}我们有，实际上，专门用来形容这宗教的词语，
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.62,0:20:53.34,English,,0,0,0,,and this word is\N{\rChinese}这个词语是
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.52,0:20:58.60,English,,0,0,0,,animism, okay? Animism.\N{\rChinese}animism，动画？
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.86,0:21:00.44,English,,0,0,0,,And what animism is,\N{\rChinese}而animism是什么，
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.44,0:21:04.70,English,,0,0,0,,is it's a very it's probably the first religion okay it's a belief\N{\rChinese}就是它是一个很古老的宗教，可能是最早的信仰
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.70,0:21:08.28,English,,0,0,0,,that each living thing whether it's a\N{\rChinese}每个有生命的东西，无论它是
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.28,0:21:11.34,English,,0,0,0,,tree a mosquito a person\N{\rChinese}树、蚊子、一个人
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.34,0:21:14.04,English,,0,0,0,,or anything that's living\N{\rChinese}或者任何有生命的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.04,0:21:17.78,English,,0,0,0,,has a soul okay\N{\rChinese}都有灵魂，好的
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.78,0:21:20.54,English,,0,0,0,,and we're all interconnected because\N{\rChinese}而我们又相互连通，因而
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.54,0:21:22.92,English,,0,0,0,,we all have souls and so\N{\rChinese}我们都有灵魂，故而
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.92,0:21:26.14,English,,0,0,0,,we must maintain balance and harmony\N{\rChinese}我们必须保持平衡与和谐
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.14,0:21:27.42,English,,0,0,0,,and so\N{\rChinese}而且
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.42,0:21:30.18,English,,0,0,0,,um many of the print of religions\N{\rChinese}嗯，许多宗教的印刷品
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.18,0:21:35.16,English,,0,0,0,,okay if you go to talk to native people in North America\N{\rChinese}好的，如果你去北美与土著人谈话
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.16,0:21:38.16,English,,0,0,0,,and South America in Australia they all have this belief but\N{\rChinese}在南美、澳洲他们都有这种信仰，但……
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.16,0:21:40.56,English,,0,0,0,,also there are many religions such as Buddhism which\N{\rChinese}还有许多宗教，如佛教也有这种信仰……
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.56,0:21:43.62,English,,0,0,0,,also has this belief okay and we believe\N{\rChinese}我们也相信……
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.62,0:21:47.70,English,,0,0,0,,that this is the first religion okay\N{\rChinese}那是第一种宗教，好的
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.70,0:21:51.32,English,,0,0,0,,so let's go over some evidence\N{\rChinese}接下来我们来看看一些证据
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.32,0:21:52.72,English,,0,0,0,,that\N{\rChinese}那
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.72,0:21:57.22,English,,0,0,0,,this is in fact what they believed okay you\N{\rChinese}这实际上就是他们所信的，好的，你们知道吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.98,0:22:01.46,English,,0,0,0,,so um a recent discovery\N{\rChinese}所以，最近我们发现的一个新发现是……
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.46,0:22:03.84,English,,0,0,0,,that we made is that\N{\rChinese}that we made isthat
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.84,0:22:07.94,English,,0,0,0,,trees talk to each other you guys do you guys know this\N{\rChinese}树木互相交流，你们知道吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.94,0:22:09.82,English,,0,0,0,,so what happens is that\N{\rChinese}于是发生的事是这样：
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.82,0:22:12.78,English,,0,0,0,,trees there are maybe thousands of trees in the forest\N{\rChinese}树木之间可能有成千棵在森林里
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.78,0:22:18.26,English,,0,0,0,,and their roots are connected through mushrooms for fungi\N{\rChinese}并且它们的根通过蘑菇连通，属于真菌体
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.26,0:22:21.32,English,,0,0,0,,and this allows us allows them to share information\N{\rChinese}这使它们能够共享信息
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.32,0:22:24.76,English,,0,0,0,,so for example what we know is that\N{\rChinese}例如我们知道的是
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.76,0:22:27.78,English,,0,0,0,,if one tree in one part of\N{\rChinese}如果森林中某棵树缺水
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.78,0:22:31.04,English,,0,0,0,,the forest lacks nutrients like water okay\N{\rChinese}其他树会把养分送过去
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.04,0:22:35.02,English,,0,0,0,,the other trees will send nutrients to\N{\rChinese}以补足它的需要
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.02,0:22:38.38,English,,0,0,0,,that tree does it make sense okay\N{\rChinese}那棵树这么做，懂了吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.38,0:22:41.16,English,,0,0,0,,so it's it's almost like the forest is one\N{\rChinese}所以它几乎像是森林是一个大脑，或者说是一个大生物体。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.16,0:22:44.88,English,,0,0,0,,big brain or one big living organism\N{\rChinese}big brain or onebig living organism
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.88,0:22:48.64,English,,0,0,0,,and they're all trying to communicate with each other another thing\N{\rChinese}并且它们都在互相交流，另外我们发现的事是……
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.64,0:22:52.60,English,,0,0,0,,that we've discovered is that if there are pests or insects\N{\rChinese}如果有害虫或昆虫攻击一棵树……
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.60,0:22:57.34,English,,0,0,0,,that attack one tree okay this tree will automatically communicate\N{\rChinese}那棵树会自动进行沟通
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.98,0:22:59.34,English,,0,0,0,,to the other trees and\N{\rChinese}给其他树木发送信号
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.34,0:23:01.24,English,,0,0,0,,these trees will start to prepare\N{\rChinese}这些树木开始准备应对抗虫攻击
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.24,0:23:05.88,English,,0,0,0,,for the pest or the attack okay\N{\rChinese}好了，准备好了
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.46,0:23:09.68,English,,0,0,0,,and the third thing which is the most interesting is\N{\rChinese}第三件事最有趣的就是……
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.68,0:23:14.50,English,,0,0,0,,that trees will recognize their own children\N{\rChinese}树会认出自己的子树
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.24,0:23:19.94,English,,0,0,0,,so if the children these children trees\N{\rChinese}于是子树们……
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.94,0:23:23.28,English,,0,0,0,,need nutrients the mother trees will send\N{\rChinese}需要养分，母树会把养分送给子树
