Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.24,0:45:56.96,English,,0,0,0,,In fact you can say that science today is our religion.\N{\rChinese}事实上，你可以说今天的科学就是我们的宗教。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.40,0:45:58.68,English,,0,0,0,,There's really no difference.\N{\rChinese}其实没什么区别。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.90,0:46:03.86,English,,0,0,0,,It's just an understanding of the world based on our imagination\N{\rChinese}这只是基于我们想象和一些证据的世界理解。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.86,0:46:05.04,English,,0,0,0,,and some evidence.\N{\rChinese}and some evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.14,0:46:10.92,English,,0,0,0,,Religion made a way for them.\N{\rChinese}宗教为他们开辟了一条道路。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.00,0:46:13.86,English,,0,0,0,,It is because religion is a social thing that we can use to create our own world.\N{\rChinese}因为宗教是社会性的事物，我们可以用它来创造自己的世界。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.88,0:46:18.06,English,,0,0,0,,It could play this role to make men take control of sense impressions\N{\rChinese}它可以扮演此角色，使人们掌握感官印象。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.06,0:46:21.56,English,,0,0,0,,and replace them with a new way of imagining the real.\N{\rChinese}并用新的方式想象现实来替代它们。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.72,0:46:24.42,English,,0,0,0,,A new kind of thought had to be created.\N{\rChinese}必须创造一种新的思维方式。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.84,0:46:29.30,English,,0,0,0,,Collective thought. So religion is our collective consciousness.\N{\rChinese}集体思维。因此，宗教就是我们的集体意识。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.78,0:46:33.60,English,,0,0,0,,It's what allows society to come into being.\N{\rChinese}它是让社会得以形成的原因。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.82,0:46:39.52,English,,0,0,0,,If collective thought alone had the power to achieve this, here is the reason.\N{\rChinese}若仅凭集体思维就能实现这一点，原因就在此。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.68,0:46:43.86,English,,0,0,0,,Create a whole world of ideals through which the world of sense reacts to. If we can create a world of ideas through which the world of sense reacts to.\N{\rChinese}通过创造一整套理想的世界，让感官世界对其作出反应。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.76,0:46:53.30,English,,0,0,0,,of ideas of health health health health health health health health\N{\rChinese}健康
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.30,0:46:57.02,English,,0,0,0,,health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health\N{\rChinese}健康
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.02,0:47:04.94,English,,0,0,0,,health health\N{\rChinese}健康
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.94,0:47:08.72,English,,0,0,0,,health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health health religion, there could be no society.\N{\rChinese}健康……宗教，若没有宗教，社会也就不存在。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.92,0:47:11.62,English,,0,0,0,,Without society, there could also be no religion.\N{\rChinese}若没有社会，宗教也可能不存在。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.34,0:47:13.70,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? You understand?\N{\rChinese}好的？你明白了吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.36,0:47:16.94,English,,0,0,0,,So the implication of all this is that\N{\rChinese}于是这一切的含义是……
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.94,0:47:20.50,English,,0,0,0,,as a human, first of all, you are not alone.\N{\rChinese}作为人类，首先你并不孤单。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.82,0:47:22.62,English,,0,0,0,,If you are alone, you're not a human.\N{\rChinese}若你独自一人，你就不是人类。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.98,0:47:26.06,English,,0,0,0,,You're a human because you live in society.\N{\rChinese}你是人类，因为你生活在社会中。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.36,0:47:29.66,English,,0,0,0,,You're with other people. And because you're with other people,\N{\rChinese}你与他人相处。因为与他人相处，
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.82,0:47:34.08,English,,0,0,0,,you must have a collective consciousness or an idea you share together.\N{\rChinese}你们必须拥有集体意识或共同的观念。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.20,0:47:35.74,English,,0,0,0,,We call this thing religion.\N{\rChinese}我们把这件事叫做宗教。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.04,0:47:38.36,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Does that make sense?\N{\rChinese}好的？这样说通吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.90,0:47:42.72,English,,0,0,0,,Is this clear to you guys? All right.\N{\rChinese}你们听懂了吗？好的。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.32,0:47:46.52,English,,0,0,0,,Any questions? Anything you are not clear about?\N{\rChinese}还有什么问题吗？还有不清楚的地方吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.32,0:47:51.02,English,,0,0,0,,Do you see how all this connects together?\N{\rChinese}你看得到这些都相互关联吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.06,0:47:55.50,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? The cave paintings is what started it.\N{\rChinese}好的？洞穴壁画就是一切的起点。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.66,0:47:57.56,English,,0,0,0,,Cave paintings is the expression of a religion.\N{\rChinese}洞穴壁画是宗教的表现形式。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.24,0:48:01.46,English,,0,0,0,,Then when the Ice Age ended, we had the chance to settle down.\N{\rChinese}随后冰河结束后，我们有机会定居。
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.88,0:48:04.34,English,,0,0,0,,We created communities to celebrate our religion.\N{\rChinese}我们创建了社区来庆祝我们的宗教。
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.52,0:48:07.04,English,,0,0,0,,That's what gave rise to activism. Okay?\N{\rChinese}这就是促成行动主义的原因。好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.70,0:48:11.72,English,,0,0,0,,And the religion that we use is probably something like this.\N{\rChinese}而我们使用的宗教大概是这样的。
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.30,0:48:13.96,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? The world is interconnected.\N{\rChinese}好的？世界相互联系。
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.52,0:48:16.58,English,,0,0,0,,There's a mother goddess that gives light to everything.\N{\rChinese}有一位母神为万物注入光明。
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.18,0:48:21.88,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Any questions?\N{\rChinese}好的？还有问题吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.70,0:48:38.48,English,,0,0,0,,Anything you are not clear about? Yeah?\N{\rChinese}还有什么不清楚的吗？嗯？
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.50,0:48:51.68,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. So\N{\rChinese}好的。那么
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.68,0:48:55.14,English,,0,0,0,,that's a good question. Okay? So the question is monotheism.\N{\rChinese}这是个好问题。好吗？问题是单神论。
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.22,0:48:57.68,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So\N{\rChinese}好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.68,0:49:01.72,English,,0,0,0,,the three major religions of today are Christianity,\N{\rChinese}今天的三大宗教是基督教、伊斯兰教和伊斯兰教。
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.08,0:49:05.02,English,,0,0,0,,Islam, and Islam.\N{\rChinese}Islam, and Islam.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.04,0:49:07.78,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And Judaism.\N{\rChinese}好的？还有犹太教。
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.12,0:49:11.38,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? They're all monotheistic, meaning they believe in one God.\N{\rChinese}好的？它们都是单神论的，意思是它们相信只有一位神。
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.30,0:49:16.88,English,,0,0,0,,So this is actually a very recent innovation.\N{\rChinese}所以这实际上是最近的创新。
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.96,0:49:21.92,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So back\N{\rChinese}好吗？回到之前。
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.92,0:49:25.54,English,,0,0,0,,then, they wouldn't have a concept of\N{\rChinese}于是，他们就没有权力平衡的概念。你明白吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.38,0:49:28.82,English,,0,0,0,,power hierarchy. Do you understand?\N{\rChinese}power hierarchy.Do you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.18,0:49:32.04,English,,0,0,0,,They wouldn't understand that the mother goddess\N{\rChinese}他们不懂母神是万神之首。
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.56,0:49:35.64,English,,0,0,0,,is the greatest God of all.\N{\rChinese}is the greatestGod of all.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.68,0:49:38.14,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? They could only think like the stars.\N{\rChinese}好的？他们只能像星星一样思考。
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.36,0:49:39.92,English,,0,0,0,,Right? There's no hierarchy in the stars.\N{\rChinese}对吗？星星里没有层级。
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.26,0:49:42.40,English,,0,0,0,,They're all over the place. Okay?\N{\rChinese}它们都散在四方。
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.56,0:49:45.78,English,,0,0,0,,So maybe the mother goddess gives birth to our world, but\N{\rChinese}于是母神可能孕育了我们的世界，但……
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.78,0:49:47.66,English,,0,0,0,,maybe there's another God that gives birth to another world.\N{\rChinese}也许还有另一位神孕育了另一个世界。
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.72,0:49:50.10,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So they wouldn't think in terms of hierarchy.\N{\rChinese}于是他们就不会以层级来思考。
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.26,0:49:53.28,English,,0,0,0,,We think in terms of hierarchy today because of monotheism.\N{\rChinese}我们今天以单神论为因，按层级思考。
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.92,0:49:55.48,English,,0,0,0,,But back then, they wouldn't think so.\N{\rChinese}但在那时，他们就不这么想。
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.26,0:49:58.98,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Does that make sense? Okay?\N{\rChinese}这样说对吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.74,0:50:03.10,English,,0,0,0,,So maybe today,\N{\rChinese}于是今天，
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.60,0:50:04.82,English,,0,0,0,,you can think of a pyramid.\N{\rChinese}你可以把它想成金字塔。
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.02,0:50:07.18,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? There's people at the top.\N{\rChinese}好了？顶端有人。
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.48,0:50:10.64,English,,0,0,0,,But back then, they would think like it's a river.\N{\rChinese}但在那时，他们会把它想成一条河流。
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.48,0:50:13.00,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? We're all part of the river.\N{\rChinese}好了？我们都是河流的一部分。
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.06,0:50:15.02,English,,0,0,0,,It's a cycle. It just goes in circles.\N{\rChinese}它是一个循环，便在圈圈转转。
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.04,0:50:19.26,English,,0,0,0,,And there's no differentiation or there's no power hierarchy.\N{\rChinese}并且没有差异也没有权力层级。
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.94,0:50:22.36,English,,0,0,0,,Things go wrong when\N{\rChinese}事物出错时
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.36,0:50:25.82,English,,0,0,0,,there's conflict inside this river.\N{\rChinese}当这条河流内部出现冲突。
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.94,0:50:30.02,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? When people don't do things they're supposed to be doing.\N{\rChinese}好了？人们不做他们应该做的事时。
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.28,0:50:34.08,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And what, and these things are what?\N{\rChinese}好了？然后什么，接着这些事又是什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.00,0:50:36.78,English,,0,0,0,,The world. What are things that\N{\rChinese}世界。事物是什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.78,0:50:41.06,English,,0,0,0,,defy the mother goddess or go against the mother goddess?\N{\rChinese}抵抗母神还是去对抗母神？
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.82,0:50:48.32,English,,0,0,0,,How about incest? Right?\N{\rChinese}关于同父同母？对吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.00,0:50:52.68,English,,0,0,0,,How about killing animals without making the proper sacrifices?\N{\rChinese}不做适当祭祀就杀动物？
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.56,0:50:56.40,English,,0,0,0,,Right? So you just kill the animals, but\N{\rChinese}对吗？你只杀了动物，却不去洞里祈求它们归来。
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.40,0:51:00.44,English,,0,0,0,,you don't go in the cave to pray for their return.\N{\rChinese}好了？换句话说，在这个世界里，宗教是基于你不会死去的事实。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.26,0:51:05.78,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So in other words, in this world, religion is based on the fact that you're not going to die.\N{\rChinese}Okay? So in other words, in this world, religionis based on the fact that you're not going to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.78,0:51:09.52,English,,0,0,0,,And this is basically ritual. And\N{\rChinese}这基本上是仪式。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.52,0:51:12.36,English,,0,0,0,,this is something that we'll study next class, how religion is just ritual.\N{\rChinese}接下来我们会研究，宗教只是仪式。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.76,0:51:15.48,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Just, just habits and practices and actions.\N{\rChinese}就是习惯、做法和动作。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.00,0:51:19.16,English,,0,0,0,,Any more questions? That's a great question, by the way.\N{\rChinese}还有别的问题吗？顺便说一句，这是个好问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.28,0:51:22.90,English,,0,0,0,,But monotheism is something that we will look at very closely in future classes.\N{\rChinese}但单神论是我们将在后续课中仔细研究的内容。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.16,0:51:26.20,English,,0,0,0,,And it's very important because it's a basis for our society.\N{\rChinese}它非常重要，因为它是我们社会的基础。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.30,0:51:28.66,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Any, any other questions?\N{\rChinese}好的？还有别的问题吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.94,0:51:32.34,English,,0,0,0,,Yeah? I noticed that last class, God,\N{\rChinese}嗯？我在上节课里注意到了，God，
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.54,0:51:35.68,English,,0,0,0,,you can't really be uncoversive because, you know,\N{\rChinese}你真的不能是无所不知的，因为，你知道，
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.32,0:51:39.88,English,,0,0,0,,Yes. Yes.\N{\rChinese}是的。是的。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.40,0:51:50.82,English,,0,0,0,,We can't live in a cave, though.\N{\rChinese}我们还是不能住在洞里。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.54,0:51:54.56,English,,0,0,0,,Right? You can't live in a cave.\N{\rChinese}对吧？你可以住在洞里。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.76,0:51:57.22,English,,0,0,0,,You can only go there now and then.\N{\rChinese}你只能时不时去那里。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.70,0:51:59.10,English,,0,0,0,,There's no oxygen in a cave.\N{\rChinese}洞里没有氧气。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.26,0:52:00.68,English,,0,0,0,,It's too dark. It's too cold.\N{\rChinese}太暗了，太冷了。
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.84,0:52:02.10,English,,0,0,0,,You can't live there.\N{\rChinese}你在那里住不了。
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.18,0:52:06.68,English,,0,0,0,,Right? So, you're right in\N{\rChinese}对吧？所以，你在……
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.68,0:52:08.90,English,,0,0,0,,that, okay, if a cave were livable,\N{\rChinese}那，好吧，如果洞能住的话，
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.24,0:52:13.82,English,,0,0,0,,they could build farms around that cave.\N{\rChinese}他们可以在那座洞旁建农场。
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.18,0:52:17.72,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So,\N{\rChinese}好的？所以，
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.72,0:52:19.16,English,,0,0,0,,okay, that's actually a great question.\N{\rChinese}好吧，这其实是个很好的问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.38,0:52:22.36,English,,0,0,0,,Besides caves, what are some other portals in the world?\N{\rChinese}除了洞穴，还有哪些其他门户？
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.96,0:52:28.58,English,,0,0,0,,What are some other portals in the world that have, like, spiritual energy besides caves?\N{\rChinese}除了洞穴，还有哪些其他门户拥有类似灵能的自然能量？
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.14,0:52:32.50,English,,0,0,0,,In nature. In nature.\N{\rChinese}在自然中。
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.50,0:52:35.32,English,,0,0,0,,If you were back then, you would think that this place is special\N{\rChinese}如果你当时在这里，你会觉得这个地方很特别
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.32,0:52:39.22,English,,0,0,0,,because it both connects our world and spirit world.\N{\rChinese}因为它既连通我们世界，也连通灵界
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.44,0:52:43.56,English,,0,0,0,,And these places would be mountaintops, right?\N{\rChinese}而这些地方就是山顶，对吧
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.12,0:52:48.50,English,,0,0,0,,Mountaintops. Guess what?\N{\rChinese}山顶。猜猜是什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.24,0:52:52.06,English,,0,0,0,,Govle Tepe was on a mountaintop, okay?\N{\rChinese}Govle Tepe 就在山顶上，明白吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.52,0:52:55.04,English,,0,0,0,,Where else would there be portals?\N{\rChinese}还有哪里会出现门户？
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.32,0:53:00.70,English,,0,0,0,,Rivers, okay? Rivers.\N{\rChinese}河流，好吗？河流。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.08,0:53:05.36,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, does that make sense? These are places that\N{\rChinese}好的，这样说通吗？这些地方是……
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.36,0:53:10.12,English,,0,0,0,,people would think are portals into another world and therefore they are special.\N{\rChinese}人们会认为它们是通往另一世界的门户，因此它们很特别。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.28,0:53:14.64,English,,0,0,0,,And we find that when they settled down and built agriculture,\N{\rChinese}我们发现，当他们定居下来并发展农业时，他们在山顶上建造，也在河流周围建造。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.00,0:53:17.24,English,,0,0,0,,they did so on mountaintops and they did so around rivers.\N{\rChinese}好的？这样说通吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.78,0:53:19.32,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Does that make sense?\N{\rChinese}Okay? Does thatmake sense?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.80,0:53:22.70,English,,0,0,0,,But not caves because you couldn't actually live in caves.\N{\rChinese}但不是洞穴，因为你实际上住不在洞穴里。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.06,0:53:30.30,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Does that\N{\rChinese}好吗？这是否……
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.30,0:53:32.18,English,,0,0,0,,answer your question? Yes.\N{\rChinese}回答了你的问题吗？是的。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.22,0:53:35.82,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. Is it possible to live in a cave?\N{\rChinese}好的。可以住在洞里吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.32,0:53:39.78,English,,0,0,0,,You can't live in a cave. There's no food and it's cold and it's wet.\N{\rChinese}你可以住在洞里。没有食物，冷又湿。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.34,0:53:42.78,English,,0,0,0,,Oh, great question, okay?\N{\rChinese}哦，好的问题，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.92,0:53:44.96,English,,0,0,0,,So they lived outside in tents.\N{\rChinese}于是他们住在帐篷外面。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.90,0:53:47.28,English,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes, but not in the cave.\N{\rChinese}哦，是的，但不是住在洞里。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.42,0:53:48.68,English,,0,0,0,,No, no, you can't live in a cave.\N{\rChinese}不，不，你可以住在洞里。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.76,0:53:50.66,English,,0,0,0,,There's no oxygen. Okay?\N{\rChinese}没有氧气。好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.42,0:53:56.02,English,,0,0,0,,Any more questions? Okay.\N{\rChinese}还有问题吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.54,0:54:01.26,English,,0,0,0,,So your question actually makes me think of a point I want to end the class with, okay?\N{\rChinese}你的问题让我想到一个点，我想用来结束这节课，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.26,0:54:04.42,English,,0,0,0,,So today we think\N{\rChinese}今天我们认为
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.42,0:54:08.78,English,,0,0,0,,that we are either economic animals,\N{\rChinese}我们是经济动物，
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.96,0:54:14.16,English,,0,0,0,,economic animals or biological animals.\N{\rChinese}经济动物还是生物动物。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.00,0:54:18.54,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So the person who\N{\rChinese}好的？那位把我们介绍为经济动物的那个人是卡尔·马克思，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.54,0:54:21.68,English,,0,0,0,,introduced us, like\N{\rChinese}他把我们介绍为经济动物的那个人是卡尔·马克思，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.68,0:54:25.50,English,,0,0,0,,who introduced to us the idea that we are economic animals is Karl Marx, okay?\N{\rChinese}那位把我们介绍为经济动物的那个人是卡尔·马克思，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.70,0:54:30.10,English,,0,0,0,,And his argument is that we are driven by our need to have money,\N{\rChinese}而他的论点是我们被需要钱的欲望驱动，
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.24,0:54:32.42,English,,0,0,0,,okay? And that's what we're doing. That's what we believe today, right?\N{\rChinese}好吧？这就是我们正在做的事。今天我们就是这么认为的，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.50,0:54:35.66,English,,0,0,0,,You're in school because you want to get good grades so\N{\rChinese}你上学是因为想拿好成绩
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.66,0:54:40.40,English,,0,0,0,,you can go get into a good university and then you can go get a good job, okay?\N{\rChinese}你可以去读好大学，然后去找好工作，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.32,0:54:43.64,English,,0,0,0,,Now, there are other people who believe that\N{\rChinese}现在，还有一些人认为
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.64,0:54:46.52,English,,0,0,0,,we are biological animals and these are people,\N{\rChinese}我们是生物动物，这些人是……
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.60,0:54:49.38,English,,0,0,0,,people are called evolutionary biologists.\N{\rChinese}人们被称为进化生物学家。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.94,0:54:51.64,English,,0,0,0,,They are inspired by Charles Darwin.\N{\rChinese}他们受到查尔斯·达尔文的启发。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.02,0:54:53.52,English,,0,0,0,,So the idea here is that\N{\rChinese}所以这里的想法是……
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.52,0:54:59.04,English,,0,0,0,,we are motivated by our desire to spread our genes,\N{\rChinese}我们被想要传播基因的欲望驱动，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.36,0:55:01.58,English,,0,0,0,,okay? So if I'm a man,\N{\rChinese}所以如果我是男人，
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.72,0:55:05.00,English,,0,0,0,,I want to sleep with as many women as possible because\N{\rChinese}我想和尽可能多的女人同床，因为
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.00,0:55:09.04,English,,0,0,0,,if I sleep with as many women as possible, I spread my genes, right?\N{\rChinese}如果我和尽可能多的女人同床，我就能传播我的基因，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.46,0:55:13.58,English,,0,0,0,,But if you're a woman, you want to find a man\N{\rChinese}如果你是女人，你会想找一个能忠于你的男人
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.58,0:55:15.96,English,,0,0,0,,who will be loyal to you because\N{\rChinese}who will be loyal to you because
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.96,0:55:18.82,English,,0,0,0,,the cost of childbearing,\N{\rChinese}育儿成本，
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.06,0:55:22.08,English,,0,0,0,,childrearing is very high, okay?\N{\rChinese}育儿成本很高，
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.62,0:55:24.64,English,,0,0,0,,Does it make sense? So and\N{\rChinese}这样说对吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.64,0:55:29.54,English,,0,0,0,,we'll be discussing both these theories more for the next class.\N{\rChinese}我们将在下节课更深入讨论这两种理论。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.54,0:55:33.20,English,,0,0,0,,Throughout the semester, okay? The argument I want to make to you today is\N{\rChinese}整个学期都如此，今天我要给你们的论点是：
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.20,0:55:36.40,English,,0,0,0,,that no, we are first\N{\rChinese}不，我们首先是……
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.40,0:55:39.86,English,,0,0,0,,and foremost a religious animal.\N{\rChinese}首先是宗教动物。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.62,0:55:44.48,English,,0,0,0,,We have the fundamental need to understand why we are here.\N{\rChinese}我们有基本的需求去理解我们为何在此。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.66,0:55:47.56,English,,0,0,0,,We have a fundamental need to connect with everyone, okay?\N{\rChinese}我们有基本的需求去与大家相连，好的？
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.70,0:55:50.56,English,,0,0,0,,To connect with other people. But that does not mean\N{\rChinese}与他人相连。但这并不意味着我们不是经济和生物动物。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.56,0:55:55.20,English,,0,0,0,,that we are not economic and biological animals, okay?\N{\rChinese}它们相互作用。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.34,0:55:56.86,English,,0,0,0,,They all interplay together.\N{\rChinese}They all interplay together.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.78,0:55:59.48,English,,0,0,0,,Do you understand? So\N{\rChinese}你明白了吗？所以
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.48,0:56:02.56,English,,0,0,0,,what we'll see later in the semester is that\N{\rChinese}接下来学期我们会看到的是
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.56,0:56:04.36,English,,0,0,0,,you might have a religion, but\N{\rChinese}你可能有宗教，但
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.36,0:56:08.10,English,,0,0,0,,this religion is not meeting your economic and biological needs.\N{\rChinese}这宗教并不能满足你的经济和生物需求。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.24,0:56:11.40,English,,0,0,0,,Then you have to either abandon the religion or change your religion, okay?\N{\rChinese}于是你要么放弃它，要么改宗教，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.24,0:56:16.02,English,,0,0,0,,But we'll also know that the economic need is not enough.\N{\rChinese}但我们也会知道，单靠经济需求是不够的。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.22,0:56:20.20,English,,0,0,0,,You also need religion. So there is an interplay between economics,\N{\rChinese}你也需要宗教。所以经济、生命和宗教之间存在相互作用。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.62,0:56:22.30,English,,0,0,0,,biology, and religion.\N{\rChinese}好的，这就是推动人类历史的原因。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.68,0:56:25.80,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, and that's what drives human history.\N{\rChinese}Okay, and that's whatdrives human history.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.98,0:56:28.12,English,,0,0,0,,This is something that we will learn more about.\N{\rChinese}这是一件我们将进一步学习的事。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.12,0:56:29.42,English,,0,0,0,,Next week, okay?\N{\rChinese}下周，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.48,0:56:32.56,English,,0,0,0,,Sorry, next week. Okay?\N{\rChinese}抱歉，下周。行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.58,0:56:40.14,English,,0,0,0,,So, yeah, any more questions? Okay.\N{\rChinese}好了，另外还有问题吗？好的。
